ENTRY       EC 2.4.1.269                Enzyme
NAME        mannosylglycerate synthase
CLASS       Transferases;
            Glycosyltransferases;
            Hexosyltransferases
SYSNAME     GDP-mannose:D-glycerate 2-alpha-D-mannosyltransferase
REACTION    GDP-mannose + D-glycerate = GDP + 2-O-(alpha-D-mannopyranosyl)-D-glycerate [RN:R09666]
ALL_REAC    R09666
SUBSTRATE   GDP-mannose [CPD:C00096];
            D-glycerate [CPD:C00258]
PRODUCT     GDP [CPD:C00035];
            2-O-(alpha-D-mannopyranosyl)-D-glycerate
COMMENT     Rhodothermus marinus can also form mannosylglycerate via a two-step pathway catalysed by EC 2.4.1.217 (mannosyl-3-phosphoglycerate synthase) and EC 3.1.3.70 (mannosyl-3-phosphoglycerate phosphatase) [1]. Depending on experimental conditions mannosylglycerate synthase is more or less specific for the GDP-mannose and D-glycerate [1,2].
